 starts with a first violent period (<10 hr) with fast re-accretion\nor ejection from the system. A second period is found to be more sensitive to\nthe launching site than the first one. During this second period, ejecta will\neither re-accrete or being ejected from the system, depending both on their\nsizes and on their average survival time in close proximity of the binary\ncomponents.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Aug 2017 03:40:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-16"}
